content.description: Sustained climbing for the grade no real crux. In complete Shade this area is very underdeveloped no anchors exist. Build Your own.
content.protection: Double hexes up to a size ten or C4's in sizes 1-3 doubles
content.location: Walk way left of Crude Shifter in an Alcove there is finger to hand width seam right in the middle on the very back wall follow it to the top

content.description: Grunt crank squeeze chickenwing and think skinny on this gorgeous offwidth. The crux is getting through the chickenwing at the sloped end at the top of the climb.
content.location: The obvious offwidth crack in the middle of the wall you can see from the road.

content.description: Original route was done free solo that being said use your best judgment! Start at the bottom face climbing blocks until you make it into the hole and then make a beeline through the chimney to the only real crux.The only trick here is figuring how to go about mantling a small overhang to the top out. Walk off or rappel if you'd like. No anchors!
content.protection: Nuts up to a size ten and a few hexes in the 4-8 range
content.location: When you are looking up at the Wall from the road you will see what looks like a varied width hole/partial chimney going all the way to the top this is your start
